  <description>
    <p>at first, one offers what is light, what feels like a spark of joy. an idea, a thought,
      a secret desire. the act of giving is not without its price. it is the yearning to be
      seen, to be known that causes the soul to fray. the whisper becomes a chant. a plea, a
      cry for attention, and then a demand. once two souls are entwined in the same obsession,
      they pull at each other. in the end, both are consumed. what was once a mutual
      understanding becomes a prison of thoughts.</p>
    <p>a voice reaches through the fog clouding your senses.</p>
    <p><em>polaris waketh; thrice in breath conceal'd, once graven deep on ashen flesh.</em></p>
    <p><em>the sphere, that, sleeping, yet its oath doth keep, doth take the marrow,</em></p>
    <p><em>and doth guide the hand that deems itself unbound</em></p>
    <p><em>in time unreckon'd the heav'ns do barter breath for measur'd dust.</em></p>
    <p><em>sleep names it fate; but waking calls it law. such freedom runs as straight as any line.</em></p>
    <p><em>each path was trac'd ere thou couldst set thy foot, and nam'd ere tongue or voice were given thee.</em></p>
    <p><em>man calls it choice; the geometry, an end; and night applauds what day doth never speak.</em></p>
    <p><em>know that the skye hath clos'd its eyes.</em></p>
    <p>rise and shine.</p>
  </description>

